fields.name: Cactus Plant
fields.description: Cacti and succulent plants have become increasingly popular among plant enthusiasts, and rightfully so. If youre looking for the perfect combination of aesthetics and ease of maintenance, succulents are your match made in heaven! Create your low-maintenance oasis indoors with cacti and succulents.

fields.name: Flowering Plants
fields.description: Indoor flowering plants bring vibrant colors and natural beauty into your home. From elegant peace lilies to cheerful ixora, these plants add a touch of joy and fragrance to any space. Discover the enchanting world of indoor flowering plants and create a blooming oasis indoors.

fields.name: Indoor Plants
fields.description: Indoor plants bring stunning & vibrant aesthetics along with a wide array of benefits to any space. Elevate your living or office space with a variety of indoor house plants grown and treated with utmost care just for you!

fields.name: Outdoor Plants
fields.description: Plants that need low maintenance and grow up easily on the outside. Plants give us oxygen and absorb carbon dioxide during the photosynthesis process, but also reduce stress, anxiety, and tiredness and give us relaxation.

fields.name: Zz Hybrid Plants
fields.description: The ZZ Plant is a classic indoor houseplant that proudly flaunts its indestructible nature. Low maintenance and fuss-free, the Zamioculcas zamiifolia is perfect for new or busy gardeners.

fields.name: Bamboo Palm Plant
fields.description: Its lush green foliage swaying daintily in the breeze is sure to remind you of tropical resorts. The stunning green leaves grow directly from the stem and over time the spread of the plant increases to fill up the pot.

fields.name: Petra croton
fields.description: The croton Petra (Codiaeum variegatum Petra) is an evergreen shrub native to southern Asia and the western Pacific islands.In other climates, croton can be grown in containers and kept indoors during cold weather.

fields.name: Thyme Ball Topiary
fields.description: Bring a lively feel to any room in your home with this artificial boxwood topiary ball tree decoration.

fields.name: Christmas Cactus Coral
fields.description: The Coral Red Christmas Cactus welcomes the holiday season with its classic coral-red blossoms.

fields.name: Dahlia
fields.description: One of the great things about dahlia container gardening is that you can use a variety of plants to create beautiful displays. When choosing plants for containers, its important to consider their size and how well they will grow in a limited space.

fields.name: Calibrachoa Mini Famous Dark Blue
fields.description: calibrachoas, also called million bells, look like mini-petunias, but botanists often debate whether theyre a variety of petunias or a different genus. Luckily, gardeners dont have to stress over what theyre called. We can just enjoy them for their variety of colors and patterns, which include stripes, pinwheels, splashes and speckles. You can find single or double calibrachoas, which look like mini roses.

fields.name: Pink Rose
fields.description: A pink rose is considered a symbol of appreciation. When someone has done a great job for you. So you can thank him by giving a pink rose in appreciation. Apart from this, whenever love or happiness arises in your mind towards someone, then you can also give pink rose to him. These pink rose flowers look very beautiful in appearance and they are also very fragrant.

fields.name: Heliconia Tropic Fleur Stems
fields.description: Tropic fleur heliconia are a type of flower that resembles a bird of paradise.  The flowers are a delicate yellow with touches of orange color. This is a tall and wide bloom. This flower will add both height and some width to any Hawaiian flower arrangement. They have a long stem. They open with three to five bracts. They bloom year round. They also add beauty to any landscape as a plant.

fields.name: French lavender
fields.description:
Lavandula Stoechas French Lavender
A small aromatic evergreen shrub with grey- green leaves and beautiful fragrant purple flowers.

fields.name: Geranium
fields.description: Geraniums are easy to grow and maintain in most homes, and they're available in a variety of sizes and colors. They can be grown indoors or outdoors, and many are great for hanging on window sills. Geraniums are typically perennial plants, but they can also be annual plants.
